==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interact
<hw>In`ter*act"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>inter-</ets> + <ets>act</ets>. Cf. <er>Entr'acte</er>.]</ety>
<def>A short act or piece between others, as in a play; an interlude;
hence, intermediate employment or time.</def>
<rj><au>Chesterfield.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interact</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Interact
<hw>In`ter*act"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To act upon each other;
<as>as, two agents mutually <ex>interact</ex></as>.</def>
<rj><au>Emerson.</au> <au>Tyndall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interaction</ent>⟦br⟧
